When working on web UI code, follow the accessibility guidelines in SKILL.md.

Key requirements:
- Every interactive element needs keyboard access
- Every image needs alt text (or alt="" for decorative)
- Focus indicators must be visible — never outline:none without a replacement
- Touch targets minimum 24x24px, prefer 44x44px
- Color is never the only indicator
- Animations respect prefers-reduced-motion
- Dynamic content uses ARIA live regions

Reference files:
- SKILL.md: Full WCAG 2.2 guidance by disability domain
- reference/accessibility.css: Production CSS utilities
- reference/patterns.md: Copy-paste JS/HTML patterns
- scripts/: 10 audit scripts (Python stdlib, no pip needed)
